messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full HTTP request path:
  /request/accept/{id}

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The controller method is annotated with:
  @RequestMapping(value = "/request/accept/{id}", method = RequestMethod.POST)
  which explicitly maps only the POST method to the path "/request/accept/{id}" and declares a path variable named "id" (mapped by @PathVariable(value = "id") long id).
- There is no class-level @RequestMapping on RegisterRequestController, so the full path is exactly "/request/accept/{id}" (no additional prefix).
- I determined allowed methods strictly from the source annotation (per your instruction). The mapping explicitly allows POST only; therefore POST = true and all other listed methods = false. (I did not assume any implicit/automatic framework behaviors such as automatic HEAD/OPTIONS handling.)
